  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Food assistance to the most vulnerable conflict affected people in the northeast Nigeria</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this project is to help IDPs, returnees, refugees, and local communities meet their basic foods and nutrition needs during and in the aftermath of shocks. This WFP project provides 1) sector-specific unconditional cash-transfers to 26,592 people and 2) conditional cash vouchers for 58,547 people. The project provides life-saving assistance to 232,066 people, including 30,224 women, 13,197 men, 105,742 children, and 1,363 persons with disabilities.</narrative>
  </description>
